The paper presents techniques for parallelizing membership tests for DFAs, which involves algorithms and data structures for efficient string matching. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions regular expressions and the PCRE library, which are related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses load balancing and profiling, which are topics in computer architecture (cs.AR) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions exploiting structural DFA properties, which is related to control theory and systems (cs.SY).
